The Paleocene climate was, much like in the Cretaceous, [[tropical]] or [[subtropical]],&lt;ref name="Hooker"/&gt;&lt;ref name=wilf/&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{cite journal|first=M. A.|last=Akhmetiev|year=2007|title=Paleocene and Eocene floras of Russia and adjacent regions: Climatic conditions of their development|journal=Paleontological Journal|volume=41|issue=11|pages=10321039|doi=10.1134/S0031030107110020}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{cite journal|first=M. A.|last=Akhmetiev|first2=V. N.|last2=Beniamovsky|year=2009|title=Paleogene floral assemblages around epicontinental seas and straits in Northern Central Eurasia: proxies for climatic and paleogeographic evolution|journal=Geologica Acta|volume=7|issue=1|pages=297309|doi=10.1344/105.000000278}}&lt;/ref&gt; and the poles were [[temperate]]&lt;ref name=williams/&gt; and ice free&lt;ref name=brea2011&gt;{{cite journal|first=M.|last=Brea|first2=S. D.|last2=Matheos|first3=M. S.|last3=Raigemborn|first4=A.|last4=Iglesias|first5=A. F.|last5=Zucol|first6=M.|last6=Prmparo|year=2011|title=Paleoecology and paleoenvironments of Podocarp trees in the Ameghino Petrified forest (Golfo San Jorge Basin, Patagonia, Argentina): Constraints for Early Paleogene paleoclimate|journal=Geologica Acta|volume=9|issue=1|pages=1328|url=https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/505/50522124003.pdf|doi=10.1344/105.000001647|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828004125/http://www.redalyc.org/pdf/505/50522124003.pdf|archive-date=28 August 2017|url-status=live}}&lt;/ref&gt; with an average global temperature of roughly {{cvt|24||25|C|F}}.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite journal|first=J.|last=Hansen|first2=M.|last2=Sato|first3=G.|last3=Russell|first4=P.|last4=Kharecha|year=2013|title=Climate sensitivity, sea level and atmospheric carbon dioxide|journal=Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society A|volume=371|issue=2001|pages=20120294|doi=10.1098/rsta.2012.0294|pmid=24043864|pmc=3785813|bibcode=2013RSPTA.37120294H|arxiv=1211.4846}}&lt;/ref&gt; For comparison, the average global temperature for the period between 1951 and 1980 was {{cvt|14|C|F}}.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/world-of-change/decadaltemp.php|title=World of Change: Global Temperatures|publisher=NASA Earth Observatory|accessdate=10 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190903121233/https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/world-of-change/decadaltemp.php|archive-date=3 September 2019|url-status=live|date=2010-12-09}}&lt;/ref&gt;

